1
00:00:01,110 --> 00:00:03,830
Hey, all you viewers out there!

2
00:00:03,830 --> 00:00:07,130
When you're watchin' Fairy Tail, make 
sure to keep the room nice and bright,

3
00:00:07,130 --> 00:00:09,220
and sit back from the screen, 'kay?

4
00:00:11,390 --> 00:00:13,950
Previously on Fairy Tail:

5
00:00:14,940 --> 00:00:16,700
Where is Erza?

6
00:00:17,270 --> 00:00:20,420
Some people who claimed to be Erza's old pals

7
00:00:20,420 --> 00:00:23,570
appeared in front of us while we 
were at Akane beach on vacation.

8
00:00:24,160 --> 00:00:27,330
Long time no see... Sister.

9
00:00:27,330 --> 00:00:29,380
And in no time at all...

10
00:00:49,220 --> 00:00:53,630
It'll be all right! I'll yell it out countless times.

11
00:00:53,630 --> 00:00:58,700
I believe your every tomorrow will be shining.

12
00:00:58,700 --> 00:01:01,050
The intersection of all people

13
00:01:01,050 --> 00:01:03,660
whose dreams have come true is one point:

14
00:01:03,660 --> 00:01:08,290
Never giving up.  And that's why we're not gonna lose!

15
00:01:08,290 --> 00:01:13,470
When it seems like you'll be blown away by the headwinds,

16
00:01:13,470 --> 00:01:15,620
grasp this hand, try to take a chance.

17
00:01:15,620 --> 00:01:18,890
Because you're not alone anymore, got it?

18
00:01:22,010 --> 00:01:24,000
Go forward, more and more!

19
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:26,520
Don't give up on your awesome dream!

20
00:01:26,520 --> 00:01:27,780
That's right, don't cry!

21
00:01:27,780 --> 00:01:29,250
Move on, my way!

22
00:01:29,250 --> 00:01:31,630
Now, with the light shining down upon you.

23
00:01:31,630 --> 00:01:33,710
Don't even think about something like giving up!

24
00:01:33,710 --> 00:01:36,140
Even if you trade being hurt again for strength.

25
00:01:36,140 --> 00:01:41,630
Your eyes, always looking straight ahead,

26
00:01:41,630 --> 00:01:45,910
can surely see the light!

27
00:02:02,510 --> 00:02:06,230
It still exists? Impossible!

28
00:02:06,230 --> 00:02:12,860
The R-system, that a black-magic cult 
plotted to construct around ten years ago...

29
00:02:13,160 --> 00:02:17,950
I thought we had destroyed 
the seven towers ourselves...

30
00:02:18,620 --> 00:02:21,030
There was an eighth tower.

31
00:02:21,030 --> 00:02:23,060
In the Ka Elm Sea.

32
00:02:23,060 --> 00:02:26,320
Looking at it... Could it be complete?

33
00:02:26,320 --> 00:02:31,490
The investigation team went missing 
right after they sent these pictures.

34
00:02:31,490 --> 00:02:33,210
They're finishing it, I guess...

35
00:02:34,610 --> 00:02:37,210
Why the R-system now?

36
00:02:37,540 --> 00:02:39,700
The Tower of Heaven.

37
00:02:39,700 --> 00:02:44,220
Not the R-system, the Tower of Heaven.

38
00:02:44,220 --> 00:02:46,560
Who cares what we call it?

39
00:02:46,560 --> 00:02:48,780
That's forbidden magic!

40
00:02:48,780 --> 00:02:51,770
If even its existence were known, 
it would cause a huge uproar!

41
00:02:51,770 --> 00:02:56,440
We must send the military 
immediately and suppress them!

42
00:02:56,440 --> 00:02:58,020
But we're up against...

43
00:02:58,020 --> 00:02:59,540
Who?

44
00:02:59,540 --> 00:03:03,530
The incident that occurred 
on Akane beach last night...

45
00:03:03,530 --> 00:03:05,930
According to reports from 
witness vacationers there,

46
00:03:05,930 --> 00:03:10,850
it seems the people occupying the 
R-system now are not that magical cult.

47
00:03:10,850 --> 00:03:13,540
So, wait! Who in the world is it?

48
00:03:13,850 --> 00:03:17,750
It sounds like that person is 
going by the name of Jellal...

49
00:03:18,050 --> 00:03:19,780
Jellal?

50
00:03:19,780 --> 00:03:23,560
Your twin brother, right, Siegrain?

51
00:03:23,560 --> 00:03:27,810
Yes... I am aware of that.

52
00:03:32,830 --> 00:03:34,240
Jellal!

53
00:03:37,710 --> 00:03:42,050
Hey, do you think the people 
trapped in the cards were saved?

54
00:03:42,050 --> 00:03:45,390
We alerted the army, so 
they're probably fine by now.

55
00:03:45,390 --> 00:03:46,950
I hope so...

56
00:03:47,310 --> 00:03:49,520
But anyway, where are we?

57
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:52,700
Perhaps Juvia's group has gotten lost...

58
00:03:52,700 --> 00:03:55,290
Natsu, are you sure they're 
in this direction?

59
00:03:56,590 --> 00:03:58,830
We're relying on your nose here!

60
00:03:58,830 --> 00:03:59,850
Get it together, man!

61
00:03:59,850 --> 00:04:02,720
I will not allow you to 
betray Gray-sama's trust!

62
00:04:03,070 --> 00:04:04,310
Damn...

63
00:04:04,310 --> 00:04:08,520
I can't believe that Erza and Happy were 
kidnapped while we were knocked out.

64
00:04:08,520 --> 00:04:09,970
How pathetic is that?!

65
00:04:09,970 --> 00:04:14,230
But how did a wizard as powerful 
as Erza-san get defeated?

66
00:04:15,110 --> 00:04:16,750
She wasn't defeated!

67
00:04:16,750 --> 00:04:18,610
You don't know a damn thing about Erza!

68
00:04:18,610 --> 00:04:20,270
I-I'm sorry!

69
00:04:20,270 --> 00:04:22,270
Gray, calm down!

70
00:04:23,330 --> 00:04:27,430
They said they were Erza's old friends.

71
00:04:27,430 --> 00:04:32,490
Even we don't know anything 
about Erza, really...

72
00:04:36,070 --> 00:04:38,960
Something feels really dangerous...

73
00:04:43,920 --> 00:04:45,010
The birds...

74
00:04:45,010 --> 00:04:46,770
What in the world is this?

75
00:04:48,060 --> 00:04:49,480
The fish too?

76
00:04:49,480 --> 00:04:51,310
This is not normal...

77
00:04:51,590 --> 00:04:54,190
This wreckage... It's from 
Fiore military ships!

78
00:04:54,190 --> 00:04:55,560
I don't like this...

79
00:04:56,350 --> 00:04:57,980
Hey, look.

80
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:02,900
That's the Tower of Heaven?

81
00:05:04,780 --> 00:05:05,990
Water Dome!

82
00:05:08,530 --> 00:05:10,830
Let us camouflage ourselves 
this way and approach.

83
00:05:10,830 --> 00:05:12,990
W-Whoa...

84
00:05:15,290 --> 00:05:18,380
You actually completed it?

85
00:05:18,770 --> 00:05:21,390
It's been eight years since then, hasn't it?

86
00:05:21,390 --> 00:05:23,720
We completed it.

87
00:05:25,300 --> 00:05:27,140
Eight years...

88
00:05:27,140 --> 00:05:29,760
You guys have all changed...

89
00:05:30,590 --> 00:05:31,910
I just can't...

90
00:05:31,910 --> 00:05:33,390
We're almost there, sheesh!

91
00:05:33,390 --> 00:05:36,170
Don't you have any sense 
of dramatic tension?!

92
00:05:37,350 --> 00:05:39,550
The ceremony will take place tonight.

93
00:05:39,550 --> 00:05:42,480
Until then, stay right here, Sister.

94
00:05:42,480 --> 00:05:43,950
Ceremony?

95
00:05:43,950 --> 00:05:46,180
You're going to activate the R-system?

96
00:05:46,610 --> 00:05:50,320
Too bad, you know? It's your 
fault for betraying us.

97
00:05:50,320 --> 00:05:54,120
Jellal is angry. But it's an honor for you.

98
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:57,660
You've been chosen as the living 
sacrifice for the ceremony!

99
00:05:58,860 --> 00:06:01,480
I guess I won't get to see you again, Sister.

100
00:06:01,480 --> 00:06:03,880
But we do it all for paradise...

101
00:06:05,340 --> 00:06:07,100
You're shaking?

102
00:06:07,100 --> 00:06:09,470
Scared of becoming a living sacrifice?

103
00:06:09,800 --> 00:06:13,300
Or is it because this is the very place...

104
00:06:18,670 --> 00:06:22,880
You think you can escape so 
easily, you little brats?

105
00:06:22,880 --> 00:06:27,530
At a time when we need to 
finish the R-System quicky!

106
00:06:27,530 --> 00:06:30,930
Hold up... At this rate we'd 
get way behind schedule.

107
00:06:30,930 --> 00:06:33,610
I was going to send you 
all to that room, but...

108
00:06:33,610 --> 00:06:38,160
Who is the one who came up with the escape 
plan? I'll only take that one away.

109
00:06:38,160 --> 00:06:40,760
Aren't we such nice guys?

110
00:06:40,760 --> 00:06:43,540
Spit it out! Who is the mastermind?

111
00:06:45,250 --> 00:06:46,660
Me...

112
00:06:45,540 --> 00:06:46,660
I'm the one!

113
00:06:46,980 --> 00:06:50,010
I made the plan, and I told them what to do!

114
00:06:52,490 --> 00:06:54,590
Of course.

115
00:06:54,590 --> 00:06:56,770
It wasn't you, I see.

116
00:06:56,770 --> 00:06:58,480
It was that girl.

117
00:06:58,480 --> 00:06:59,900
Take her away!

118
00:06:59,900 --> 00:07:03,080
No! It was me! I planned it!

119
00:07:03,080 --> 00:07:04,000
It's not Erza!

120
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:05,360
Let Erza go!

121
00:07:08,210 --> 00:07:09,890
I'll be okay...

122
00:07:10,200 --> 00:07:11,700
I'm fine...

123
00:07:11,700 --> 00:07:13,780
Erza!

124
00:07:13,780 --> 00:07:18,330
It'll be just like you said, 
Jellal... I'm not scared at all.

125
00:07:19,060 --> 00:07:20,500
Erza...

126
00:07:20,500 --> 00:07:22,450
Erza!

127
00:07:25,030 --> 00:07:27,540
Sorry about back then, Sister.

128
00:07:27,540 --> 00:07:32,120
I was the one who planned it, but I 
was scared and didn't say anything.

129
00:07:32,620 --> 00:07:35,270
It's not fair, you know?

130
00:07:37,960 --> 00:07:40,230
It's long in the past...

131
00:07:40,230 --> 00:07:45,750
Do you understand the danger of trying 
to resurrect someone using the R-system?

132
00:07:46,200 --> 00:07:50,030
You know what the R-system 
is for? I'm impressed.

133
00:07:50,030 --> 00:07:52,210
Revive System...

134
00:07:52,210 --> 00:07:56,070
To resurrect a single person using a 
large number of human sacrifices...

135
00:07:56,070 --> 00:07:58,880
It's forbidden, inhumane magic.

136
00:07:58,880 --> 00:08:02,870
Sister... Magic has always 
been at odds with humanity.

137
00:08:02,870 --> 00:08:06,750
All magic erodes one's humanity.

138
00:08:06,750 --> 00:08:10,720
That's black-magic sophism. 
You're no different from them!

139
00:08:10,720 --> 00:08:13,830
They thought this was just a 
way to reunite body with soul.

140
00:08:13,830 --> 00:08:17,220
They didn't realize it was more than just 
magic to bring someone back from the dead.

141
00:08:17,540 --> 00:08:19,840
But Jellal is different!

142
00:08:19,840 --> 00:08:23,400
He'll be leading us to heaven shortly!

143
00:08:23,400 --> 00:08:24,640
Heaven?

144
00:08:24,640 --> 00:08:29,150
When Jellal resurrects that certain 
individual, the world will be reborn.

145
00:08:29,480 --> 00:08:32,420
With us as its rulers.

146
00:08:32,420 --> 00:08:35,440
The last remnants of the cult 
who took away our freedom,

147
00:08:35,440 --> 00:08:38,310
You, my trator Sister and your friends...

148
00:08:38,310 --> 00:08:41,170
The pitiful citizens living 
their lives in ignorance!

149
00:08:41,170 --> 00:08:44,040
Those incompetent fools on the Council!

150
00:08:44,040 --> 00:08:47,770
They will all cower in 
fear, be drenched in grief!

151
00:08:47,770 --> 00:08:50,880
Then we'll take away everyone's freedom!

152
00:08:50,880 --> 00:08:55,070
We will become the rulers of the world!

153
00:09:01,810 --> 00:09:03,110
Sister...

154
00:09:06,900 --> 00:09:07,940
Sho...

155
00:09:10,470 --> 00:09:11,650
Sis!

156
00:09:13,370 --> 00:09:16,590
To think people can change so much...

157
00:09:19,570 --> 00:09:21,380
Jellal...

158
00:09:21,380 --> 00:09:22,830
Is this your doing, you fiend?

159
00:09:29,120 --> 00:09:31,340
It's all cats!

160
00:09:31,340 --> 00:09:33,320
Where am I?

161
00:09:33,320 --> 00:09:34,770
Where's Natsu?

162
00:09:35,540 --> 00:09:36,670
It's a cat-woman!

163
00:09:36,670 --> 00:09:38,400
Feelin' spiffy?

164
00:09:38,400 --> 00:09:40,300
Feelin' spiffy...

165
00:09:40,300 --> 00:09:43,100
It's a talking kitty cat!

166
00:09:43,640 --> 00:09:47,890
Millianna, why don't you 
try being more of a dandy?

167
00:09:48,420 --> 00:09:49,310
It's you!

168
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:54,090
It isn't a talking cat. It's a 
cat because it talks, get it?

169
00:09:54,090 --> 00:09:55,070
I see!

170
00:09:55,070 --> 00:09:57,070
I don't get that at all!

171
00:09:57,070 --> 00:10:00,340
And wait, where am I? Where's Natsu?

172
00:10:00,340 --> 00:10:05,080
Hey cat! That boy is probably 
kissing asphalt right now!

173
00:10:06,890 --> 00:10:09,590
No way Natsu's been done in like that!

174
00:10:09,590 --> 00:10:12,720
We have a report! Erza Scarlet has escaped!

175
00:10:12,720 --> 00:10:15,970
Escaped? Just like old times!

176
00:10:16,350 --> 00:10:18,970
There's no escape from this tower...

177
00:10:18,970 --> 00:10:19,850
Please hurry!

178
00:10:19,850 --> 00:10:22,770
Erza's here too...

179
00:10:20,820 --> 00:10:22,770
What a pain...

180
00:10:25,780 --> 00:10:27,350
Lord Jellal...

181
00:10:27,910 --> 00:10:30,400
I knew Erza would make a good woman.

182
00:10:30,400 --> 00:10:31,980
How intriguing, indeed.

183
00:10:32,320 --> 00:10:36,280
I'm looking forward to see 
who wins: Erza or myself.

184
00:10:36,280 --> 00:10:38,110
Life and death...

185
00:10:38,110 --> 00:10:42,510
A game of heaven which 
connects the past and future.

186
00:10:43,540 --> 00:10:45,610
We have to do something...

187
00:10:45,610 --> 00:10:46,750
First, gather information!

188
00:10:46,750 --> 00:10:48,200
We must dispatch the entire military!

189
00:10:48,200 --> 00:10:49,580
You bleeding-heart doves...

190
00:10:49,580 --> 00:10:50,890
What do you mean?

191
00:10:50,890 --> 00:10:52,260
Sieg, you bastard!

192
00:10:52,260 --> 00:10:54,120
Sending the military?

193
00:10:54,120 --> 00:10:56,610
What else could I call someone 
with that weak a response?

194
00:10:56,610 --> 00:10:59,010
This is dangerous... Far too dangerous!

195
00:10:59,920 --> 00:11:01,470
What are you trying to say?

196
00:11:01,470 --> 00:11:03,850
You people don't understand.

197
00:11:03,850 --> 00:11:07,600
There is only one way to destroy 
the Tower of Heaven now.

198
00:11:08,250 --> 00:11:10,280
Otherwise we are all doomed for sure.

199
00:11:10,850 --> 00:11:11,940
Etherion!

200
00:11:11,940 --> 00:11:13,130
What did you say?!

201
00:11:13,130 --> 00:11:15,150
The cross-dimensional destruction magic?!

202
00:11:15,150 --> 00:11:16,610
Are you mad?!

203
00:11:16,610 --> 00:11:18,960
You've seen its predicted 
destructive power, right?

204
00:11:18,960 --> 00:11:21,450
It has the power to destroy 
an entire country!

205
00:11:22,040 --> 00:11:24,840
Etherion is our ultimate weapon!

206
00:11:24,840 --> 00:11:27,160
It's even more dangerous 
magic than the R-system!

207
00:11:27,160 --> 00:11:28,550
However...

208
00:11:29,160 --> 00:11:34,920
But with the satellite square, 
we could target this entire area.

209
00:11:34,920 --> 00:11:39,090
And the only thing that could destroy 
such a large building is Etherion!

210
00:11:39,810 --> 00:11:41,870
I concur.

211
00:11:41,870 --> 00:11:43,710
Ultear, you too?

212
00:11:43,710 --> 00:11:46,600
There are 9 of us in total. 
Only three more are needed.

213
00:11:46,940 --> 00:11:50,780
If three more people agree 
than we fire Etherion!

214
00:11:50,780 --> 00:11:52,420
There's no time!

215
00:11:52,420 --> 00:11:55,400
We can't let him use the R-system!

216
00:11:55,400 --> 00:12:01,260
That will end with your twin brother 
Jellal losing his life, you know.

217
00:12:01,260 --> 00:12:02,770
Of course.

218
00:12:02,770 --> 00:12:06,780
That's just how terrible a system it is.

219
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:19,750
Tell me where Jellal is!

220
00:12:19,750 --> 00:12:21,500
There are a lot of lookouts...

221
00:12:21,500 --> 00:12:22,430
Should we bust in?

222
00:12:22,430 --> 00:12:25,200
No! Erza and Happy are captured!

223
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:28,230
If we don't do this right, we could 
put the two of them in danger.

224
00:12:28,230 --> 00:12:29,970
That would put us at a disadvantage.

225
00:12:29,970 --> 00:12:32,740
I've found a way in underwater.

226
00:12:32,740 --> 00:12:34,350
Really? That's great!

227
00:12:34,350 --> 00:12:35,920
I have been praised!

228
00:12:35,920 --> 00:12:38,380
Not you, but I, Juvia!

229
00:12:38,380 --> 00:12:38,860
Riiight...

230
00:12:39,790 --> 00:12:41,950
It's about ten minutes underwater.

231
00:12:41,950 --> 00:12:43,460
That ain't a problem.

232
00:12:43,460 --> 00:12:44,040
Nope.

233
00:12:44,040 --> 00:12:45,860
No way! Impossible!

234
00:12:46,210 --> 00:12:48,740
Then put this on your head.

235
00:12:48,740 --> 00:12:52,460
It's oxygen trapped in a water shell, 
so you can breath underwater.

236
00:12:52,870 --> 00:12:54,700
You're awesome!

237
00:12:54,700 --> 00:12:56,220
So... Who are you?

238
00:13:04,480 --> 00:13:06,690
So this is that base of the tower...

239
00:13:06,690 --> 00:13:08,390
Where's Erza and Happy?

240
00:13:08,390 --> 00:13:10,690
These things are pretty 
convenient, if a bit tacky...

241
00:13:10,690 --> 00:13:15,240
I made yours a bit smaller, Lucy-san, 
so I'm impressed you made it.

242
00:13:15,240 --> 00:13:16,230
Hey, wait a sec there...

243
00:13:17,390 --> 00:13:18,760
Intruders!

244
00:13:18,760 --> 00:13:19,610
Crap!

245
00:13:22,780 --> 00:13:24,370
Who are these infidels!

246
00:13:24,370 --> 00:13:25,690
Well then...

247
00:13:25,690 --> 00:13:27,070
...guess there's only one thing to do!

248
00:13:27,070 --> 00:13:27,740
Right!

249
00:13:27,740 --> 00:13:29,870
You're asking who we are?

250
00:13:29,870 --> 00:13:33,320
Your allies attacked us, 
and you don't even know?!

251
00:13:34,500 --> 00:13:36,960
We're Fairy Tail, you idiots!

252
00:13:36,960 --> 00:13:38,170
That's hot!

253
00:13:38,500 --> 00:13:41,380
Ice Make Lance!

254
00:13:40,250 --> 00:13:41,990
That's cold!

255
00:13:41,990 --> 00:13:43,370
A swimsuit!

256
00:13:42,620 --> 00:13:44,240
Thank you very much!

257
00:13:44,240 --> 00:13:46,470
Gate of the Maiden, I open thee!

258
00:13:46,750 --> 00:13:48,220
Virgo!

259
00:13:49,560 --> 00:13:51,430
You called for me, Princess?

260
00:13:51,430 --> 00:13:52,210
It's a maid!

261
00:13:52,210 --> 00:13:53,750
Who needs bikini-girl now?

262
00:13:53,750 --> 00:13:55,100
Proceed with the punishment, please...

263
00:13:55,100 --> 00:13:56,180
As you wish...

264
00:13:57,970 --> 00:13:59,450
Damn, what is she?

265
00:13:59,450 --> 00:14:01,360
Watch out, blades don't affect her!

266
00:14:01,360 --> 00:14:03,150
Take this!

267
00:14:06,190 --> 00:14:07,820
What the heck is with her?

268
00:14:07,820 --> 00:14:09,570
Drip, drip, drop...

269
00:14:10,020 --> 00:14:11,620
Water Slicer!

270
00:14:17,920 --> 00:14:19,750
We're mostly finished here.

271
00:14:19,750 --> 00:14:20,780
Seems like it.

272
00:14:20,780 --> 00:14:22,460
After making all this noise, 
do you think we'll be...

273
00:14:22,460 --> 00:14:23,830
Oh, who am I kidding...

274
00:14:23,830 --> 00:14:24,950
Do I need punishment?

275
00:14:24,950 --> 00:14:26,130
Where's the blockhead?

276
00:14:31,030 --> 00:14:32,120
And...

277
00:14:32,120 --> 00:14:34,330
They're telling us, "Come on up?"

278
00:14:34,330 --> 00:14:37,390
Lord Jellal, why are you 
inviting the intruders inside?

279
00:14:37,740 --> 00:14:40,770
I told you, remember? This is a game.

280
00:14:40,770 --> 00:14:43,080
They have cleared a stage.

281
00:14:43,080 --> 00:14:45,210
That is all.

282
00:14:45,210 --> 00:14:46,920
This makes things more interesting.

283
00:14:46,920 --> 00:14:49,510
But if we don't hurry with the ceremony...

284
00:14:49,510 --> 00:14:53,560
The ships we sunk the other day mean 
that the Council has already...

285
00:14:53,560 --> 00:14:57,760
Vidaldus, are you still worried about that?

286
00:14:58,960 --> 00:15:00,460
I-I concur!

287
00:15:00,460 --> 00:15:01,860
Elder Leiji!

288
00:15:01,860 --> 00:15:03,050
We have no choice.

289
00:15:03,050 --> 00:15:04,420
Only two more.

290
00:15:04,700 --> 00:15:06,160
There is no time.

291
00:15:06,720 --> 00:15:08,850
They can't stop me.

292
00:15:08,850 --> 00:15:11,880
Not those fools on the 
Council, that's for sure.

293
00:15:13,680 --> 00:15:15,280
Blockhead!

294
00:15:15,280 --> 00:15:16,850
Don't yell like that!

295
00:15:16,850 --> 00:15:19,060
We already made such a big mess downstairs...

296
00:15:19,060 --> 00:15:21,690
There's no reason for us to 
be sneaking around anymore.

297
00:15:21,690 --> 00:15:23,220
What are you eating?

298
00:15:23,220 --> 00:15:24,600
It looks like a meal has been prepared.

299
00:15:24,600 --> 00:15:25,790
Shall you partake, Princess?

300
00:15:25,790 --> 00:15:27,350
Um, look here...

301
00:15:27,350 --> 00:15:31,930
That door from before was operated 
by remote control through magic.

302
00:15:31,930 --> 00:15:34,120
Our presence is completely known.

303
00:15:34,120 --> 00:15:35,650
Then why in the world...

304
00:15:35,650 --> 00:15:37,650
Maybe they're challenging us?

305
00:15:37,650 --> 00:15:39,010
A challenge?

306
00:15:39,010 --> 00:15:42,720
Oh, yes, Princess... Do you think it 
is appropriate to eat in such attire?

307
00:15:42,720 --> 00:15:43,990
Appropriate?

308
00:15:43,990 --> 00:15:45,260
Let us change those clothes...

309
00:15:45,260 --> 00:15:46,450
Right here?!

310
00:15:46,450 --> 00:15:47,360
Hey, wait...

311
00:15:47,360 --> 00:15:49,510
Gray-sama! Don't look!

312
00:15:49,870 --> 00:15:52,380
These are clothes from the Spirit World.

313
00:15:53,010 --> 00:15:56,180
What do you think? I know, 
I know... I look good...

314
00:15:57,110 --> 00:15:58,730
That's pretty cute!

315
00:15:58,730 --> 00:16:00,160
Juvia is so frustrated!

316
00:16:00,160 --> 00:16:01,470
He lllikes her!

317
00:16:01,470 --> 00:16:03,210
Please don't roll your tongue...

318
00:16:03,210 --> 00:16:05,560
Where did you learn to mimic Happy?

319
00:16:06,770 --> 00:16:10,400
Meanwhile, what should I do?

320
00:16:10,400 --> 00:16:12,510
Princess, I wish you best of luck.

321
00:16:12,510 --> 00:16:14,000
Thank you, Virgo.

322
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:17,240
Speaking of which, are you sure you 
want to stay in those wet clothes?

323
00:16:17,560 --> 00:16:19,270
We'll dry them off in a jiff.

324
00:16:19,270 --> 00:16:20,740
Human drying machine!

325
00:16:20,740 --> 00:16:21,530
There they are!

326
00:16:21,530 --> 00:16:22,790
The intruders!

327
00:16:24,930 --> 00:16:26,090
Erza!

328
00:16:26,090 --> 00:16:27,450
You're safe!

329
00:16:27,840 --> 00:16:29,090
Cool...

330
00:16:30,900 --> 00:16:32,980
Why are you here?

331
00:16:32,980 --> 00:16:34,130
Why?

332
00:16:34,130 --> 00:16:36,430
Um... Juvia is...

333
00:16:36,430 --> 00:16:37,970
Go back!

334
00:16:37,970 --> 00:16:39,930
This is not a place you should have come!

335
00:16:40,710 --> 00:16:43,080
Don't go sayin' that, Erza!

336
00:16:43,080 --> 00:16:44,930
If we retreat with our 
tails between out legs,

337
00:16:44,930 --> 00:16:46,890
that'll shame the name of Fairy Tail!

338
00:16:46,890 --> 00:16:49,620
I am not going to let 
that Blockhead off easy!

339
00:16:49,620 --> 00:16:51,030
I said go back.

340
00:16:51,030 --> 00:16:51,770
But...

341
00:16:51,770 --> 00:16:53,610
Happy's been kidnapped!

342
00:16:53,610 --> 00:16:54,940
You expect me to leave him?

343
00:16:54,940 --> 00:16:55,950
Happy?

344
00:16:55,950 --> 00:16:58,320
Millianna couldn't have...

345
00:16:58,320 --> 00:16:59,910
Where is he?

346
00:16:59,910 --> 00:17:01,700
I don't know...

347
00:16:59,910 --> 00:17:01,700
The ocean?

348
00:17:01,700 --> 00:17:03,010
Okay, got it!

349
00:17:03,010 --> 00:17:04,620
What do you get?

350
00:17:04,620 --> 00:17:07,450
Happy is waiting for me!

351
00:17:07,450 --> 00:17:08,710
Natsu...

352
00:17:09,000 --> 00:17:10,260
That idiot.

353
00:17:10,260 --> 00:17:11,190
Natsu-san...

354
00:17:11,190 --> 00:17:12,550
We're going too!

355
00:17:12,550 --> 00:17:14,190
No!

356
00:17:14,190 --> 00:17:16,580
Millianna loves cats above all else.

357
00:17:16,580 --> 00:17:19,260
I cannot believe that she 
would do harm to Happy.

358
00:17:19,610 --> 00:17:22,590
I will take responsibility for 
bringing both of them back.

359
00:17:22,590 --> 00:17:24,590
You get away from here as quickly as you can.

360
00:17:24,590 --> 00:17:26,580
No! Not without you, Erza!

361
00:17:26,580 --> 00:17:28,400
This is my problem!

362
00:17:28,400 --> 00:17:30,440
I do not want to get you involved.

363
00:17:30,440 --> 00:17:33,030
It's already plenty our problem.

364
00:17:33,030 --> 00:17:34,800
You saw Natsu, right?

365
00:17:35,420 --> 00:17:39,760
Erza, what is this tower? Who is Jellal?

366
00:17:41,110 --> 00:17:43,580
I understand if you don't want to tell us...

367
00:17:43,580 --> 00:17:47,670
You said that they used to 
be your companions, right?

368
00:17:47,670 --> 00:17:51,080
But now we're your companions...

369
00:17:51,080 --> 00:17:54,390
We're on your side, no matter what Erza!

370
00:17:54,390 --> 00:17:55,840
You heard the lady.

371
00:17:56,830 --> 00:17:57,820
Go back!

372
00:17:57,820 --> 00:17:58,970
Erza...

373
00:17:58,970 --> 00:18:01,620
This isn't like you, Ms. Erza...

374
00:18:01,620 --> 00:18:05,720
You'd usually say, "Follow 
me and no complaining!"

375
00:18:05,720 --> 00:18:08,290
We'll lend you a hand.

376
00:18:08,290 --> 00:18:12,300
Even you get scared sometimes, right?

377
00:18:18,860 --> 00:18:20,030
I'm sorry.

378
00:18:20,670 --> 00:18:27,110
Whether I win or lose this battle, 
I will vanish from this world...

379
00:18:27,730 --> 00:18:28,960
What do you mean?

380
00:18:29,900 --> 00:18:32,820
This is a future I cannot oppose.

381
00:18:32,820 --> 00:18:33,810
Therefore...

382
00:18:34,620 --> 00:18:38,970
Therefore while I still exist, 
I'll tell you everything.

383
00:18:41,780 --> 00:18:44,570
The name of this tower 
is the Tower of Heaven.

384
00:18:44,570 --> 00:18:46,390
Also known as the R-system.

385
00:18:47,550 --> 00:18:49,060
More than ten years ago...

386
00:18:49,830 --> 00:18:52,690
A black-magic religious cult

387
00:18:52,690 --> 00:18:57,440
constructed it in order to cast a forbidden 
spell to resurrect someone from the dead.

388
00:18:59,190 --> 00:19:02,330
It requires a large number 
of living sacrifices.

389
00:19:02,330 --> 00:19:05,870
Also, through the slave-labor 
of the sacrificial humans,

390
00:19:05,870 --> 00:19:08,670
they amplified the magical power they needed.

391
00:19:10,230 --> 00:19:14,260
I was also one of those living 
sacrifices when I was little.

392
00:19:15,300 --> 00:19:18,640
Those who tried to escape, or rebelled...

393
00:19:18,640 --> 00:19:21,970
One by one they disappeared.

394
00:19:21,970 --> 00:19:24,850
There was no peace of mind.

395
00:19:24,850 --> 00:19:26,730
We lived in constant fear.

396
00:19:27,090 --> 00:19:30,230
Even so, I made friends 
who I could open up to.

397
00:19:30,790 --> 00:19:33,190
Even if it was for only a brief moment...

398
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:39,270
And one of the people I knew then was Jellal.

399
00:19:44,560 --> 00:19:46,160
Erza!

400
00:19:46,900 --> 00:19:48,080
Erza!

401
00:19:49,110 --> 00:19:51,300
Hey, hang in there!

402
00:19:55,010 --> 00:19:56,590
Your eye...

403
00:19:59,650 --> 00:20:02,570
What have they done... Erza...

404
00:20:02,570 --> 00:20:04,930
What did we do to deserve this, Erza?

405
00:20:05,340 --> 00:20:07,890
No!

406
00:20:09,070 --> 00:20:10,270
Jellal...

407
00:20:10,270 --> 00:20:12,560
Erza, thank goodness!

408
00:20:12,560 --> 00:20:14,900
It's okay now. I've come to save you.

409
00:20:14,900 --> 00:20:17,150
H-How?

410
00:20:21,510 --> 00:20:24,130
There's no turning back now.

411
00:20:24,960 --> 00:20:26,480
We have to fight.

412
00:20:26,820 --> 00:20:27,910
Fight?

413
00:20:31,070 --> 00:20:32,680
Damn it!

414
00:20:32,680 --> 00:20:34,470
It's the magic troops!

415
00:20:35,950 --> 00:20:38,500
I wonder if Sis is okay?

416
00:20:38,500 --> 00:20:41,590
Grandpa Rob, you came back 
alive from that room, right?

417
00:20:41,590 --> 00:20:42,870
What in the world is that place...

418
00:20:42,870 --> 00:20:46,160
I think Erza-chan should be fine...

419
00:20:46,160 --> 00:20:50,600
As long as you have a strong heart, 
they can't steal your soul.

420
00:20:50,600 --> 00:20:52,810
What is that supposed to mean?

421
00:20:51,890 --> 00:20:52,810
Get in there.

422
00:20:53,560 --> 00:20:54,890
Sis!

423
00:20:54,890 --> 00:20:56,140
Erza...

424
00:20:56,140 --> 00:20:58,430
Hey, where's Jellal?

425
00:20:56,750 --> 00:20:59,270
It's time for work!

426
00:20:58,430 --> 00:21:00,300
Leave her be.

427
00:21:00,300 --> 00:21:02,730
Just be glad she's back 
alive at a time like this...

428
00:21:02,730 --> 00:21:04,120
But...

429
00:21:04,120 --> 00:21:07,940
They must have taken a replacement.

430
00:21:07,940 --> 00:21:09,990
No more...

431
00:21:09,990 --> 00:21:12,110
I can't stand this anymore!

432
00:21:12,110 --> 00:21:13,160
Quiet down there!

433
00:21:13,160 --> 00:21:14,890
Calm down, Sho!

434
00:21:14,890 --> 00:21:18,510
It'll be okay... I'm here beside you.

435
00:21:18,510 --> 00:21:20,130
Prepare yourself.

436
00:21:20,130 --> 00:21:21,720
No!!

437
00:21:21,720 --> 00:21:22,880
We have to fight.

438
00:21:23,510 --> 00:21:24,620
Why, you...

439
00:21:24,620 --> 00:21:25,630
What are you doing?

440
00:21:28,350 --> 00:21:29,370
Hey...

441
00:21:29,370 --> 00:21:30,140
No way...

442
00:21:31,310 --> 00:21:33,720
They're rebelling!

443
00:21:34,840 --> 00:21:36,180
Erza, what are you...

444
00:21:36,180 --> 00:21:37,550
Take their weapons!

445
00:21:37,550 --> 00:21:41,260
If we obey them, or run 
away, we'll never be free!

446
00:21:41,260 --> 00:21:43,040
We have to fight!

447
00:21:43,040 --> 00:21:46,660
For our freedom, rise up and fight!

448
00:21:50,860 --> 00:21:52,960
For our freedom...

449
00:21:53,580 --> 00:21:56,080
To save Jellal... We rose up and fought.

450
00:21:56,660 --> 00:22:02,800
Jellal was our leader... He had a strong 
sense of justice, and I looked up to him.

451
00:22:03,380 --> 00:22:04,500
But...

452
00:22:06,110 --> 00:22:10,460
But it was right at that moment that Jellal 
turned into a completely different person.

453
00:22:11,540 --> 00:22:18,440
If it is possible to call a person "evil," 
then that is what I shall call Jellal.

454
00:23:56,180 --> 00:24:00,940
Natsu, have you heard a strange 
voice at night lately?

455
00:24:00,940 --> 00:24:01,920
A strange voice?

456
00:24:01,920 --> 00:24:03,490
I haven't heard anything weird myself...

457
00:24:03,490 --> 00:24:05,160
I can hear it...

458
00:24:05,160 --> 00:24:08,290
Night after night, a girl's 
voice, softly sobbing...

459
00:24:08,290 --> 00:24:09,460
Seriously?

460
00:24:09,460 --> 00:24:11,000
That sounds pretty cool!

461
00:24:11,000 --> 00:24:13,960
I don't think it's cool at all!

462
00:24:13,960 --> 00:24:16,510
Next time: Voice of Darkness!

463
00:24:16,510 --> 00:24:18,970
So, what is that poltergeist saying?

464
00:24:18,970 --> 00:24:22,070
"The rent... Oh, the rent!" etc...

465
00:24:22,070 --> 00:24:24,000
I'm pretty sure that's just Lucy.

466
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:26,250


